overview: The user initiated a project to implement a database and an admin
  dashboard for a sleep questionnaire application, referencing a Statement of
  Work. The primary goal was to store questionnaire responses, provide a
  client-facing dashboard for data access, and secure it with authentication.
  The approach involved integrating a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) via Prisma,
  creating a  model to store raw data and denormalized
  demographics, and developing API routes for saving and retrieving responses. A
  simple admin dashboard was built, featuring a login page and a table with CSV
  export functionality. Initially, a custom session management system was
  implemented, but it was later streamlined to use Next.js middleware for
  authentication, simplifying route protection and session handling. The user
  confirmed the database setup and was provided with a checklist to test the new
  functionality, including submitting a questionnaire, logging into the admin
  dashboard, and downloading a CSV report.
